comment: Anytime fans of something have a problem they shouldn't be treated as cannon fodder....any criticism comes with the job.... fans are the life blood of any superstar, movie, game, team or organization.....and the fans should always be treated 100% thoughtfully.....we need a basic rule book on how to treat fans because I think alot of people forgot or just want to skip that part of the game and they wonder why these movies aren't doing so good, even before the pandemic. You respect the fans and the fans will return the love...even when fans are angry you have to show them understanding....when the fans are mad maybe just maybe look at the product you put out first before you suggest that the fans are fucked up just for criticizing....and 1 very last important note: when you suggest that a work of art is only for 1 group of people it automatically cuts your bottom line in half...a work of art is meant to be seen by everyone and you shouldn't put a ceiling on it before it even comes out by suggesting fans who criticize the movie are racist, misogynistic or somehow just being assholes....maybe you are the asshole for insulting the fans in the first place....exactly
